A 3-year-old boy has been beaten to death and his mother's boyfriend, who fled into nearby woods following the incident, is in custody.

Sheriff's deputies were called to a home in Georgia's Forsyth County at about 11 a.m. Tuesday and found the toddler, who neighbors identified as 'Wyatt,' unresponsive.

Deputy Doug Rainwater said the mom's boyfriend fled into the woods behind the neighborhood after calling the child's mother to say something was wrong.

