The mother rushed home and immediately called 911, Rainwater told the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.

The child was rushed to Northside Hospital-Forsyth but despite resuscitation attempts, he was pronounced dead.

More than three dozen deputies used dogs to track the man into the woods and he was accosted just before 1:45 p.m. near the intersection of Georgia 369 and Georgia 400.

He was taken into custody and Rainwater said investigators are questioning him and the mother, both of whom haven't been identified.

